# demo

A demo service

> Scaffolded by [`springup`](https://github.com/springup-cli/springup) v0.1.0.

## Tech stack

| Concern | Choice |
| --- | --- |
| Framework | Spring Boot 3.5.0 |
| Language | java (21) |
| Build tool | maven |
| Packaging | JAR |
| Architecture | layered |



## Dependencies

- `web`
- `data-jpa`
- `postgresql`



## Prerequisites

- JDK 21+

- (Optional) Maven 3.9+ — or just use the bundled `./mvnw` wrapper.


## Build & run


```bash
# Build + run tests
./mvnw verify

# Run the app locally (dev profile)
./mvnw spring-boot:run -Dspring-boot.run.profiles=dev


# Run the packaged JAR
java -jar target/demo-*.jar --spring.profiles.active=dev
```

The service starts on `http://localhost:8080`.


Health check: `GET http://localhost:8080/api/health`


## Configuration


Configuration lives in `src/main/resources/application.properties`.


## Docker


No Dockerfile was generated. Add one with `springup add docker` (future) or write one manually.




## CI


No CI was generated. Add one with `springup add ci` (future) or write one manually.


## Architecture


Layered architecture (`controller / service / repository / dto / entity / exception`):

```
src/main/java/com/example/demo/
├── controller/    # REST controllers
├── service/       # Business logic
├── repository/    # Spring Data JPA repositories
├── dto/           # Request / response DTOs (incl. ApiResponse<T>)
├── entity/        # JPA entities
└── exception/     # GlobalExceptionHandler + custom exceptions
```

A sample CRUD slice (`SampleEntity` → `SampleRepository` → `SampleService` → `SampleController`)
demonstrates the layering end-to-end. Replace it with your own domain.


